main event: Two sets of bright white navigation lights were observed in the sky over Phoenix, Arizona on November 29, 1955.
interesting points: The objects appeared stationary in relation to each other, but ascended like rockets, resolving into two separate lights, climbing higher and higher until lost to sight.
The objects moved too fast and too high to be aircraft, and much too fast for objects in orbit.
The total sighting time was estimated to be 10-15 seconds.
The witness had experience in aircraft identification and astronomy.
The witness called the FAA Radar Center in Albuquerque, New Mexico to report the sighting.
sighted object: two sets of bright white navigation lights
witnesses: a witness with experience in aircraft identification and astronomy
photographs: no photographs included in the report
